-- MTS Gains After Resuming Operations in Turkmenistan
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-07-26T22:00:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/mts-gains-in-new-york-after-resuming-operations-in-turkmenistan.html
OAO Mobile TeleSystems (MBT) , Russia’s
biggest mobile phone company by subscribers, rose the most in
seven weeks in the U.S. after the company said it is resuming
operations in  Turkmenistan .  American depositary receipts of MTS, as the company is
known, advanced 4.7 percent to $18.36 in New York, the most
since June 6. The stock gained for the first time in five days.  MTS said it reached an agreement with the Central Asian
state’s authorities and signed an accord for five years, which
may be extended for an additional five, MTS said in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
 hpavliva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
